    "problemStatement": "Chef gave you a sequence of integers a1,a2,\u2026,aNa_1, a_2, \\dots, a_Na1\u200b,a2\u200b,\u2026,aN\u200b and 333 integers KKK, mmm and xxx. Let's define the following functions:\nG(i1,\u2026,iK)=gcd(ai1,\u2026,aiK)G(i_1, \\ldots, i_K) = \\mathrm{gcd}\\left(a_{i_1}, \\dots, a_{i_K}\\right)G(i1\u200b,\u2026,iK\u200b)=gcd(ai1\u200b\u200b,\u2026,aiK\u200b\u200b)\nSx(i1,\u2026,iK)=ai1x+ai2x+\u2026+aiKxS_x(i_1, \\ldots, i_K) = a_{i_1}^x + a_{i_2}^x + \\ldots + a_{i_K}^xSx\u200b(i1\u200b,\u2026,iK\u200b)=ai1\u200bx\u200b+ai2\u200bx\u200b+\u2026+aiK\u200bx\u200b\nPm(i1,\u2026,iK)=(ai1\u22c5ai2\u22c5\u2026\u22c5aiK)mP_m(i_1, \\ldots, i_K) = \\left(a_{i_1} \\cdot a_{i_2} \\cdot \\ldots \\cdot a_{i_K}\\right)^mPm\u200b(i1\u200b,\u2026,iK\u200b)=(ai1\u200b\u200b\u22c5ai2\u200b\u200b\u22c5\u2026\u22c5aiK\u200b\u200b)m\nW(T)=smallest\u2009\u2009prime\u2009\u2009divisor\u2009\u2009of\u2009\u2009P1(T)W(T) = \\mathrm{smallest\\,\\, prime\\,\\, divisor\\,\\, of\\,\\, } P_1(T)W(T)=smallestprimedivisorofP1\u200b(T)\n\nChef wants you to compute the sum of G(T)\u22c5W(T)\u22c5Sx(T)\u22c5Pm(T)G(T) \\cdot W(T) \\cdot S_x(T) \\cdot P_m(T)G(T)\u22c5W(T)\u22c5Sx\u200b(T)\u22c5Pm\u200b(T) over all KKK-tuples of indices T=(i1,i2,\u2026,iK)T = (i_1, i_2, \\ldots, i_K)T=(i1\u200b,i2\u200b,\u2026,iK\u200b) such that ij\u2208{1,2,\u2026,N}i_j \\in \\{1, 2, \\ldots, N\\}ij\u200b\u2208{1,2,\u2026,N} for each valid jjj (there are NKN^KNK of these KKK-tuples). Since this sum could be enormous, compute it modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7.",
